            "answer_text": "Some of the problem is related to the passenger's height. I notice this when I sit in my husband's favorite recliner. The headrest hits him in exactly the right spot, but for me it is never quite right, and pushes my head forward. The same thing happens on airplanes. The seat is designed for an \"average\" passenger and especially if you are shorter than average that headrest will not fit you properly. ",
